sk.stuba.fiit.perconik.core.persistence.serialization

Interface SerializedResourceData

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Annotable, AnnotableRegistration, Registration, ResourceRegistration
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ResourcePersistenceData

    public interface SerializedResourceData
extends ResourceRegistration
    Interface implemented by optional holders of serialized Resource data. Instances of classes implementing this interface provide optional access to Resource object that can be serialized and deserialized. These instances usually hold a serializable resource. A serializable resource is a concrete implementation of Resource interface also implementing the Serializable interface.

    Note: Holding serialized resource data or a serializable resource object is optional.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Pavol Zbell
